1
00:02:16,753 --> 00:02:18,475
The world is reeling.

2
00:02:18,575 --> 00:02:22,234
Errol Flynn, movie star, matinee idol,
notorious ladies' man,

3
00:02:22,334 --> 00:02:24,695
is dead at the age of 50.

4
00:02:24,795 --> 00:02:26,363
The hero of a generation,

5
00:02:26,463 --> 00:02:30,201
equally known for his swashbuckling
in public and in private.

6
00:02:30,301 --> 00:02:34,472
He died true to form, in the arms
of a much younger girlfriend.

7
00:02:34,572 --> 00:02:39,145
Now, all of America is asking,
"Who is the girl?"

8
00:02:58,561 --> 00:03:00,433
Just got a few questions out here.

9
00:03:01,699 --> 00:03:03,167
Just a couple questions.

10
00:03:03,567 --> 00:03:05,669
All right,
first let's all just move back

11
00:03:05,769 --> 00:03:07,905
and give Miss Aadland some room,
would you, please?

12
00:03:08,005 --> 00:03:09,640
- Miss Aadland!
- Miss Aadland! There she is!

13
00:03:09,740 --> 00:03:11,609
Is it true that Errol Flynn
died in your arms?

14
00:03:11,709 --> 00:03:13,644
- What were his last words?
- How long had you known him?

15
00:03:13,744 --> 00:03:15,279
Miss Aadland,
are you going to the funeral?

16
00:03:15,379 --> 00:03:17,681
Miss Aadland, did Flynn leave you
anything in his will?

17
00:03:17,781 --> 00:03:18,844
Miss Aadland!

18
00:03:19,715 --> 00:03:21,783
- Beverly!
- How old are you?

19
00:03:21,883 --> 00:03:23,449
- Bev!
- Are you going to the funeral?

20
00:03:23,549 --> 00:03:24,722
Beverly.

21
00:03:24,822 --> 00:03:27,188
Miss Aadland, what were
you doing in Vancouver?

22
00:03:28,057 --> 00:03:29,693
Don't push! Don't push!

23
00:03:29,893 --> 00:03:32,229
- She's gonna faint.
- Beverly!

24
00:03:32,329 --> 00:03:34,028
Please, just get back!

25
00:03:34,330 --> 00:03:35,543
Hey!

26
00:03:36,299 --> 00:03:38,014
Beverly!

27
00:03:41,404 --> 00:03:42,571
What was your relationship...

28
00:03:58,821 --> 00:04:00,391
The girl fainted.

29
00:04:00,491 --> 00:04:03,679
Yeah, it's a pretty crazy scene
over here.

30
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:06,593
Hey, let me call you back later.

31
00:04:10,533 --> 00:04:11,602
Excuse me, ma'am.

32
00:04:11,702 --> 00:04:12,903
- Are you the mother?
- Yes.

33
00:04:13,003 --> 00:04:15,706
Hi, I'm Tedd Thomey, here's my card.
I was wondering if you could just...

34
00:04:15,806 --> 00:04:18,276
- A few questions about your daughter?
- I'm in a hurry. I...

35
00:04:18,376 --> 00:04:19,844
Is it true that she was mentioned
in the will?

36
00:04:19,944 --> 00:04:22,246
Well, he wanted to make sure
she was very well looked after.

37
00:04:22,346 --> 00:04:23,581
Well, do you think she's pregnant?

38
00:04:23,681 --> 00:04:25,149
- Pregnant?
- We just saw her faint.

39
00:04:25,249 --> 00:04:28,085
We're talking a big age difference here,
do you think that they were in love?

40
00:04:28,185 --> 00:04:32,523
Oh, head over heels in love, yes.
I mean, it was her first love, and his last.

41
00:04:32,623 --> 00:04:36,362
I couldn't have done anything to stop it,
even if I wanted to. It was all predestined.

42
00:04:36,462 --> 00:04:41,190
Mrs. Aadland, look this way.
Here, take this. And dab your eye.

43
00:04:42,198 --> 00:04:45,682
- Looks great. Thanks.
- Do you need another one?

44
00:05:05,521 --> 00:05:08,592
- Baby, are you close?
- Going as fast as I can.

45
00:05:08,692 --> 00:05:11,244
- Let me see.
- Hold on.

46
00:05:15,064 --> 00:05:17,935
I thought we agreed on the bolero dress,
the Paula Lynn.

47
00:05:18,035 --> 00:05:19,349
What's wrong with this?

48
00:05:19,449 --> 00:05:23,704
Nothing. It's adorable, but it
makes you look too young. Trust me.

49
00:05:27,410 --> 00:05:29,746
Now, this is much better.

50
00:05:29,846 --> 00:05:32,994
- They're here already.
- All right, Herb.

51
00:05:33,249 --> 00:05:34,585
Here you go.

52
00:05:34,685 --> 00:05:38,155
I've canceled your dance class
for the next three weeks.

53
00:05:38,255 --> 00:05:41,436
But you can still make the acting class
as long as you don't go over time.

54
00:05:41,536 --> 00:05:43,827
- Do I have to?
- Yes, you do.

55
00:05:43,927 --> 00:05:45,796
I said I'd go bowling
with some of the gang.

56
00:05:45,896 --> 00:05:48,232
Well, never mind about that.

57
00:05:48,332 --> 00:05:51,335
You know, Mrs. Morgan is so excited.

58
00:05:51,435 --> 00:05:55,737
She couldn't believe when I told her
that you were in a movie with Gene Kelly.

59
00:05:56,774 --> 00:06:00,477
- I'm only in the chorus line.
- I know, but that's just for now.

60
00:06:00,577 --> 00:06:03,581
I mean, what's that Natalie Wood
girl have, that you don't have?

61
00:06:03,681 --> 00:06:06,714
- Cab's waiting.
- All right, Herb.

62
00:06:06,916 --> 00:06:10,521
- Now, remember your manners...
- But don't fade into the woodwork.

63
00:06:10,621 --> 00:06:12,487
That's my girl. Beautiful.

64
00:06:14,156 --> 00:06:15,990
- Bye bye.
- Bye, sweetie.

65
00:06:58,034 --> 00:07:00,771
Excuse me,
may I talk to you for a moment?

66
00:07:00,871 --> 00:07:02,429
Sure.

67
00:07:02,529 --> 00:07:05,108
- How do you do?
- Very well, thank you.

68
00:07:05,208 --> 00:07:09,747
I'm Orry Kelly, doing costumes on Too Much,
Too Soon over on stage eight,

69
00:07:09,847 --> 00:07:13,317
and there's a certain someone over there,
who would very much like to meet you.

70
00:07:13,417 --> 00:07:16,289
- Who?
- Errol Flynn.

71
00:07:16,819 --> 00:07:18,603
You know who he is, don't you?

72
00:07:18,803 --> 00:07:20,363
Sure.

73
00:07:20,823 --> 00:07:22,573
Robin Hood.

74
00:07:35,271 --> 00:07:38,933
- Are you decent?
- Never, come in.

75
00:07:46,949 --> 00:07:51,555
Hello, there. I'm Errol Flynn,
and who might you be?

76
00:07:51,655 --> 00:07:54,291
I'm Beverly Aadland.
Pleased to meet you.

77
00:07:54,391 --> 00:07:58,562
Pleased to meet you.
And what exactly do you do, Miss Aadland?

78
00:07:58,662 --> 00:08:00,063
Actor, singer, dancer.

79
00:08:00,163 --> 00:08:03,400
Really? All three, that's extraordinary.
Triple threat, yes.

80
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:05,734
I envy you, I never could dance myself.

81
00:08:05,834 --> 00:08:08,372
- Or sing.
- Or act.

82
00:08:08,472 --> 00:08:11,141
How long have you been
in this profession, Miss Aadland?

83
00:08:11,241 --> 00:08:12,643
Forever, pretty much.

84
00:08:12,743 --> 00:08:15,596
- A seasoned professional.
- I guess.

85
00:08:15,696 --> 00:08:19,266
- I'd better be going.
- What? No, no, no, no. Stay, Orry. Stay.

86
00:08:19,366 --> 00:08:23,467
Isn't she an exquisite creature?
She'd be perfect, don't you think?

87
00:08:24,103 --> 00:08:26,971
Yes. Yes, Errol. Perfect.

88
00:08:33,379 --> 00:08:34,515
Aadland residence.

89
00:08:34,615 --> 00:08:36,116
- <i>Hi, Mom.</i>
- Hi.

90
00:08:36,216 --> 00:08:38,952
I can't make acting class tonight.
I have an audition.

91
00:08:39,052 --> 00:08:41,922
- <i>What kind of an audition?</i>
- It's for a play.

92
00:08:42,022 --> 00:08:45,158
"Master of" something.
It's with Errol Flynn.

93
00:08:45,258 --> 00:08:47,987
- Who?
- <i>Errol Flynn.</i>

94
00:08:48,895 --> 00:08:51,098
- Don't be nervous, just be yourself.
- Okay.

95
00:08:51,198 --> 00:08:53,200
<i>- And don't smoke in front of him.</i>
- Okay, Mom.

96
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:55,402
- Be a good listener.
- Okay, okay.

97
00:08:55,502 --> 00:08:56,637
- Okay.
<i>- Bye.</i>

98
00:08:56,737 --> 00:08:58,236
<i>Bye.</i>

99
00:09:02,374 --> 00:09:05,109
- Would you care for one?
- No, thanks.

100
00:09:05,878 --> 00:09:09,116
You'll get a kick out of this lodge
where we're going. It's a...

101
00:09:09,216 --> 00:09:12,718
It belongs to Huntington Hartford,
he's the producer of the play.

102
00:09:13,654 --> 00:09:16,613
Yes, my wife and I are separated.

103
00:09:17,690 --> 00:09:21,659
And he took pity
on this homeless vagabond.

104
00:09:29,935 --> 00:09:32,005
I'll be sad to leave it.

105
00:09:32,105 --> 00:09:37,441
Every good, true vigorous feeling I have,
gathers impulsively around him.

106
00:09:37,543 --> 00:09:40,213
I know, I must conceal my sentiments.

107
00:09:40,313 --> 00:09:44,751
I must smother hope. I must remember
that he cannot care much for me.

108
00:09:44,851 --> 00:09:48,507
I must repeat continually,
that we are forever sun... sunder...

109
00:09:48,607 --> 00:09:50,656
- Sundered!
- Sundered.

110
00:09:50,756 --> 00:09:53,175
- Sundered.
- Very good.

111
00:09:53,275 --> 00:09:55,415
Very good, indeed.

112
00:09:56,328 --> 00:09:58,192
Do you like that speech?

113
00:10:00,766 --> 00:10:02,300
Well...

114
00:10:02,868 --> 00:10:05,259
I think it's kind of corny.

115
00:10:07,439 --> 00:10:08,853
It is, isn't it?

116
00:10:10,743 --> 00:10:14,314
<i>Come on. There must have been
something that made you feel suspicious.</i>

117
00:10:14,414 --> 00:10:17,985
<i>Well, if it turns out to be one of us,
I'm gonna wring his rotten red neck.</i>

118
00:10:18,085 --> 00:10:20,588
- <i>Yeah, maybe you are wringing it.</i>
- I'll get it.

119
00:10:20,688 --> 00:10:23,457
<i>I'm a first class
United States American, see?</i>

120
00:10:23,557 --> 00:10:25,956
<i>Don't even hint I got...</i>

121
00:10:29,328 --> 00:10:31,814
- Aadland residence.
- <i>Hi, Mom.</i>

122
00:10:31,914 --> 00:10:34,801
- How's it going?
- Everything's fine, we're having dinner.

123
00:10:34,901 --> 00:10:37,337
Dinner? Well, then the audition
must have gone very well.

124
00:10:37,437 --> 00:10:39,403
<i>Yeah, I guess.</i>

125
00:10:39,772 --> 00:10:43,510
It's just the two of you,
he's not getting any funny ideas, is he?

126
00:10:43,610 --> 00:10:45,712
Mom, of course not.

127
00:10:45,812 --> 00:10:47,948
<i>You come straight home afterwards.</i>

128
00:10:48,048 --> 00:10:51,752
Okay, there's someone
who wants to say hello to you.

129
00:10:52,252 --> 00:10:56,523
<i>Hello, is this the charming mother
of a very charming young lady?</i>

130
00:10:56,623 --> 00:10:59,090
I'd recognize that voice anywhere.

131
00:10:59,926 --> 00:11:03,330
Very nice to meet you
over the phone, Mrs. Aadland.

132
00:11:03,430 --> 00:11:06,327
I would love to meet you in person, though.
Perhaps you could come round to the lodge,

133
00:11:06,427 --> 00:11:08,335
sometime next week.

134
00:11:08,535 --> 00:11:10,704
Thank you. That sounds lovely.

135
00:11:10,804 --> 00:11:13,707
<i>Wonderful. I'll have my man call you
and make all the arrangements.</i>

136
00:11:13,807 --> 00:11:16,243
- It's a plan.
- Who is it?

137
00:11:16,343 --> 00:11:18,211
It's the producer of the play.

138
00:11:18,311 --> 00:11:21,881
What the hell play is auditioning
at this hour?

139
00:11:22,237 --> 00:11:23,247
<i>We're chasing...</i>

140
00:11:25,419 --> 00:11:27,821
Are you sure you won't have
some champagne?

141
00:11:27,921 --> 00:11:30,623
It'll make the movie
go down much easier.

142
00:11:30,723 --> 00:11:32,425
No, thank you.

143
00:11:36,128 --> 00:11:38,161
Okay, maybe I will.

144
00:11:39,999 --> 00:11:41,379
All right.

145
00:11:43,102 --> 00:11:45,636
You've seen it this color before?

146
00:11:45,771 --> 00:11:47,706
Millions of times.

147
00:11:47,806 --> 00:11:51,241
- Millions?
- It's a figure of speech.

148
00:11:53,579 --> 00:11:56,758
You're like a little sprite.
You know that?

149
00:11:56,858 --> 00:12:00,117
A wood nymph.
Has anyone ever told you that?

150
00:12:00,586 --> 00:12:02,389
- No.
- Oh, definitely.

151
00:12:02,489 --> 00:12:06,059
Yes, in fact, I think
I'm going to call you Woodsey.

152
00:12:06,459 --> 00:12:08,695
- Do you like that?
- I don't know.

153
00:12:08,795 --> 00:12:11,611
Would you think about it
and let me know?

154
00:12:12,598 --> 00:12:15,666
- Thanks, Woodsey.
- I didn't say "yes," yet.

155
00:12:16,102 --> 00:12:19,840
But it's such a perfect name for you.
Woodsey.

156
00:12:19,940 --> 00:12:21,527
I don't think so.

157
00:12:21,827 --> 00:12:24,274
Oh, Woodsey,

158
00:12:25,978 --> 00:12:28,612
you have to face your destiny.

159
00:12:28,714 --> 00:12:30,666
My destiny.

160
00:12:47,733 --> 00:12:49,976
You're extraordinary.

161
00:13:08,620 --> 00:13:10,047
Errol.

162
00:13:29,408 --> 00:13:31,761
You got any smokes?

163
00:13:32,144 --> 00:13:33,513
No.

164
00:13:33,613 --> 00:13:36,880
There's a gas station down on Sunset.

165
00:13:38,317 --> 00:13:41,651
- Can we stop?
- Sure.

166
00:13:41,787 --> 00:13:43,754
You okay?

167
00:13:44,556 --> 00:13:46,038
Yeah.

168
00:13:47,793 --> 00:13:49,860
Yeah, I guess.

169
00:13:56,468 --> 00:13:59,036
Is he like that with all the girls?

170
00:14:00,539 --> 00:14:02,106
What do you mean?

171
00:14:05,411 --> 00:14:07,401
That's what I thought.

172
00:14:17,089 --> 00:14:19,814
Oh, baby, I was so worried.

173
00:14:20,426 --> 00:14:22,028
- Hi.
- How was it?

174
00:14:22,128 --> 00:14:23,563
Oh, it was fine.

175
00:14:23,663 --> 00:14:26,600
- Yeah?
- I don't think I got the part, though.

176
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:29,867
Why do you say that? He took you to dinner,
you must be in the running.

177
00:14:29,969 --> 00:14:32,505
- I guess.
- So what's he like, Errol Flynn?

178
00:14:33,005 --> 00:14:35,942
He was nice. He talked a lot.

179
00:14:36,042 --> 00:14:39,579
- And were you a good listener?
- Yes, I was.

180
00:14:39,679 --> 00:14:42,146
But I'll talk to you about it later,
I'm really tired.

181
00:15:01,767 --> 00:15:03,236
I've seen all your movies.

182
00:15:03,336 --> 00:15:07,307
The Sea Hawk was my favorite.
I saw it, like, five times.

183
00:15:07,407 --> 00:15:09,409
Really? I could barely
get through it once.

184
00:15:09,509 --> 00:15:13,013
Oh, but you're such a great actor,
Mr. Flynn. Thank you.

185
00:15:13,313 --> 00:15:16,049
Woodsey, I've been
looking for you all day.

186
00:15:16,149 --> 00:15:19,485
I wanted to ask you out
for dinner, if you...

187
00:15:19,585 --> 00:15:23,690
Look, I'm terribly sorry that things
got so out of hand at the audition.

188
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:25,492
Is that what it was? An audition?

189
00:15:25,592 --> 00:15:30,827
Look, I'm so sorry.
I mistook you completely.

190
00:15:30,929 --> 00:15:34,931
- I didn't realize...
- I'm late.

191
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:39,810
Well, why haven't you seen him?

192
00:15:40,572 --> 00:15:42,342
He's on a different soundstage.

193
00:15:42,442 --> 00:15:45,245
Well, when you do see him,
I want you to remind him

194
00:15:45,345 --> 00:15:47,278
that I'm very excited about meeting him.

195
00:15:48,714 --> 00:15:50,817
- He did say he wanted to meet me.
- Okay.

196
00:15:50,917 --> 00:15:53,553
Yeah, okay. Well...

197
00:15:53,653 --> 00:15:57,287
Make sure that you have lunch,
you're getting too skinny.

198
00:15:58,457 --> 00:16:02,095
One and two and three and four.

199
00:16:02,195 --> 00:16:06,263
One and two and three and four.

200
00:16:47,973 --> 00:16:50,176
Sorry to intrude, ladies.

201
00:16:50,276 --> 00:16:53,543
Now at last I find out
where you've been hiding.

202
00:16:53,712 --> 00:16:56,446
I was hoping to have a word
with Miss Aadland.

203
00:16:58,083 --> 00:16:59,817
If you don't mind.

204
00:17:03,655 --> 00:17:05,589
Excuse us, please.

205
00:17:07,159 --> 00:17:08,794
Who was that?

206
00:17:09,094 --> 00:17:10,661
Here.

207
00:17:15,634 --> 00:17:19,838
Beverly, I can't stop
thinking about you.

208
00:17:19,938 --> 00:17:23,143
I lie awake, nights. Really.
I... I haven't slept in days.

209
00:17:23,243 --> 00:17:25,712
I don't understand what the point is.
You already got what you wanted.

210
00:17:25,812 --> 00:17:27,793
What I want is to get to know you,
to spend time with you,

211
00:17:27,893 --> 00:17:30,183
enjoy your company, that's all.

212
00:17:30,283 --> 00:17:33,853
Look, I know my reputation
precedes me, but I promise you,

213
00:17:33,953 --> 00:17:35,989
whatever you've read in the press,

214
00:17:36,089 --> 00:17:41,326
I swear, the man standing before you now,
is a different animal entirely.

215
00:17:41,426 --> 00:17:43,293
Please, believe me.

216
00:17:46,632 --> 00:17:48,155
What's that?

217
00:17:49,034 --> 00:17:51,869
Oh, it's a... It's a question mark.

218
00:17:52,337 --> 00:17:55,541
Yes, I know. Why?

219
00:17:55,641 --> 00:17:58,611
Because I question everything.

220
00:17:58,711 --> 00:18:01,815
Even at my age,
I'm still trying to figure it all out.

221
00:18:01,915 --> 00:18:05,418
I... just never believe
what I've been told.

222
00:18:05,518 --> 00:18:07,854
Someone tells me, "You can't do that,"
I say, "Why the hell not?"

223
00:18:07,954 --> 00:18:11,591
And then I go ahead and bloody well do it,
and I get into a bit of trouble.

224
00:18:11,691 --> 00:18:15,125
But I'm just endlessly curious.

225
00:18:16,061 --> 00:18:19,200
I'm especially curious about you.

226
00:18:32,644 --> 00:18:34,948
- Who is it?
- Hi, Mrs. Aadland. It's Tedd Thomey.

227
00:18:35,048 --> 00:18:38,885
- If I could just ask you a few questions.
- Why don't you all go to hell?

228
00:18:38,985 --> 00:18:42,889
It's Tedd Thomey, ma'am. We met
at the airport. I gave you my card.

229
00:18:42,989 --> 00:18:46,590
Yeah, I'm not a reporter,
I'm the guy that writes the books.

230
00:18:47,726 --> 00:18:50,296
Look, I know it's been
a difficult time for you, ma'am.

231
00:18:50,396 --> 00:18:53,697
I'm a straight-up guy,
I won't misrepresent you.

232
00:18:56,368 --> 00:18:59,539
Things have been so crazy
since Errol died.

233
00:19:00,039 --> 00:19:02,172
It's been a very hard time for me.

234
00:19:04,676 --> 00:19:08,745
- I was very close to him, too, you know.
- I can understand, yeah.

235
00:19:10,582 --> 00:19:14,618
- Are you okay?
- Oh, I have an artificial leg.

