00:34:30,402 --> 00:34:35,040
and those that are left behind on the
garbage heap, the has-beens, the wannabes.

467
00:34:35,140 --> 00:34:38,109
This is her shot, you can't say no.

468
00:34:38,209 --> 00:34:41,746
If you do, she's gonna resent you
for the rest of her life,

469
00:34:41,846 --> 00:34:44,118
and I will, too.

470
00:34:45,383 --> 00:34:47,650
You owe me this.

471
00:34:51,022 --> 00:34:52,789
Oh, Flo.

472
00:34:53,424 --> 00:34:56,238
You always had your way with that girl.
You kept me out...

473
00:34:56,338 --> 00:34:58,598
I never kept you out of it,
you weren't in it because...

474
00:34:58,698 --> 00:35:00,563
Let me finish!

475
00:35:01,163 --> 00:35:02,941
Damn you!

476
00:35:05,636 --> 00:35:07,603
Take her if you want.

477
00:35:08,639 --> 00:35:10,395
But that's it.

478
00:35:11,142 --> 00:35:15,144
I'll wash my hands of the both of you.
You're on your own.

479
00:35:41,139 --> 00:35:44,944
Oh, look, Bev. I've always wanted
to come to New York.

480
00:35:45,977 --> 00:35:50,580
You know, not many mothers
would do what I'm doing.

481
00:35:51,782 --> 00:35:53,616
I know.

482
00:35:55,219 --> 00:35:56,800
I love you, Mom.

483
00:35:58,422 --> 00:36:00,923
Oh, I love you too, baby.

484
00:36:06,330 --> 00:36:08,197
Mom.

485
00:36:09,033 --> 00:36:12,601
Errol wanted me to talk to you
about the sleeping arrangements.

486
00:36:14,171 --> 00:36:15,974
Okay.

487
00:36:16,075 --> 00:36:20,676
He wanted me to tell you that I'd be
sleeping in his room most nights.

488
00:36:21,379 --> 00:36:24,216
- What?
- It's the way he wants it.

489
00:36:24,316 --> 00:36:27,567
That may be the way he wants it, but that
doesn't mean that's what he's going to get.

490
00:36:27,667 --> 00:36:29,952
Mom, come on.

491
00:36:31,189 --> 00:36:33,122
He's Errol Flynn.

492
00:36:35,459 --> 00:36:38,530
- You better not say anything.
- Don't tell me what to do. I trusted you.

493
00:36:38,630 --> 00:36:40,632
- Mom, don't embarrass me.
- Just stop whining.

494
00:36:40,732 --> 00:36:44,066
- Yes.
- Yes, we are here to see Mr. Errol Flynn.

495
00:36:46,270 --> 00:36:49,639
It was leaving for Hong Kong.
So, we got on it...

496
00:36:51,346 --> 00:36:53,313
- Hi, how are you?
- Good.

497
00:36:53,413 --> 00:36:55,077
Woodsey.

498
00:36:56,214 --> 00:36:58,250
- Everyone, may I have your attention.
- May I take your coat?

499
00:36:58,350 --> 00:37:01,953
I wish to present the marvelous
Mrs. Florence Aadland

500
00:37:02,053 --> 00:37:05,924
and her exquisite daughter, Beverly.
It's their first time in New York.

501
00:37:06,024 --> 00:37:10,295
- So I hope you give them a warm welcome.
- Welcome.

502
00:37:10,395 --> 00:37:12,194
- Hello, Beverly.
- Hello.

503
00:37:12,730 --> 00:37:14,766
- Oh, God, I missed you.
- I missed you.

504
00:37:14,866 --> 00:37:17,733
- Thank God you're here.
- I'll put these in the closet, ma'am.

505
00:37:18,302 --> 00:37:21,740
- Hey, there, I'm John Ireland.
- The actor?

506
00:37:21,980 --> 00:37:23,773
Yes, indeed.

507
00:37:24,141 --> 00:37:26,211
Your daughter's very lovely.

508
00:37:26,311 --> 00:37:28,911
Yes, thank you.

509
00:37:33,517 --> 00:37:37,022
Hello, Florence. I know.
I know you're angry with me

510
00:37:37,122 --> 00:37:39,423
and you have every reason to be.

511
00:37:39,523 --> 00:37:43,062
- I am the devil incarnate.
- I could have you thrown in jail.

512
00:37:43,162 --> 00:37:46,224
- Please, don't joke about this.
- I'm not joking. You lied to me.

513
00:37:46,324 --> 00:37:50,536
You blatantly lied to me, to my face
about what you were up to with my baby.

514
00:37:50,636 --> 00:37:55,107
I thought it was perfectly obvious.
What did you want me to say?

515
00:37:55,207 --> 00:37:57,809
That I was in over my head
with your daughter?

516
00:37:57,909 --> 00:38:00,979
Your beautiful clever daughter.
Whom you've groomed so carefully

517
00:38:01,079 --> 00:38:04,182
- to seem older than her years?
- Oh, now, I'm the one to blame?

518
00:38:04,282 --> 00:38:08,787
No. No. No. No more than I am.
But, if I deceived you

519
00:38:08,887 --> 00:38:12,888
you deceive me as well,
not to mention the rest of Hollywood.

520
00:38:16,527 --> 00:38:18,272
Florence.

521
00:38:20,631 --> 00:38:24,803
I love Beverly as much as
I've ever loved anyone.

522
00:38:24,903 --> 00:38:30,109
And for some reason she loves me,
really loves me.

523
00:38:30,209 --> 00:38:35,277
So, please, try to find it in your heart
to forgive me for both our sakes.

524
00:38:35,579 --> 00:38:41,250
And I think if you'll admit it, you always
knew what was going on, didn't you?

525
00:38:42,787 --> 00:38:44,589
All right, what are you
love birds doing in here?

526
00:38:48,193 --> 00:38:50,796
- I'm sorry.
- No, no, we're just, catching up.

527
00:38:50,896 --> 00:38:52,576
Right, Flo?

528
00:38:55,466 --> 00:38:59,004
So here we are. Enough for everyone.

529
00:38:59,104 --> 00:39:02,708
<i>Seeing them together again
I realized that it was a love match.</i>

530
00:39:02,808 --> 00:39:06,078
<i>I saw that he genuinely
cared for her, very much,</i>

531
00:39:06,178 --> 00:39:10,816
<i>but as I turned it over and over in my mind
I realized it could go either way.</i>

532
00:39:11,416 --> 00:39:14,686
<i>The liaison with Errol could be
very good for Beverly's career,</i>

533
00:39:14,786 --> 00:39:17,656
<i>but it could also be a disaster.</i>

534
00:39:17,756 --> 00:39:21,660
<i>They weren't married after all, and if
the press realized what was going on,</i>

535
00:39:21,760 --> 00:39:23,995
<i>it would be a page one scandal.</i>

536
00:39:24,095 --> 00:39:25,826
<i>I knew we were playing
with dynamite here</i>

537
00:39:25,926 --> 00:39:29,468
<i>and it all had to be handled
very carefully.</i>

538
00:39:29,568 --> 00:39:34,503
<i>I didn't want our lives turning
from an A picture into a B movie.</i>

539
00:39:40,544 --> 00:39:44,413
Look darling, Dag Hammarskjöld,
he's a great man.

540
00:39:47,651 --> 00:39:49,521
- You know who he is?
- Yes.

541
00:39:49,621 --> 00:39:50,889
Who is he?

542
00:39:50,989 --> 00:39:53,892
He works at the United Nations,
he's like a secretary.

543
00:39:53,992 --> 00:39:57,960
- Yes, secretary-general to be precise.
- Yeah.

544
00:39:58,662 --> 00:40:00,832
I am going to get you a tutor
while you're here.

545
00:40:00,932 --> 00:40:05,169
- No, tutors are boring.
- Well...

546
00:40:05,269 --> 00:40:07,172
I like things just the way they are.

547
00:40:07,272 --> 00:40:10,442
Well, I'm gonna get you some
decent books to read at any rate.

548
00:40:10,542 --> 00:40:14,513
Something with a little more
literary merit than the funnies.

549
00:40:14,613 --> 00:40:18,567
Oh, no, come on, don't spoil it.

550
00:40:18,949 --> 00:40:20,719
It's the most fun I've ever had.

551
00:40:21,119 --> 00:40:24,588
Really, you don't miss
Los Angeles, your friends?

552
00:40:24,688 --> 00:40:29,027
No. I'm like a windup toy there.

553
00:40:29,127 --> 00:40:32,698
Go to this audition, go to this dance class,
go to this voice coach...

554
00:40:32,898 --> 00:40:35,731
- Do you even like show business?
- Yes.

555
00:40:35,866 --> 00:40:38,537
- Really?
- Kind of. It's fun.

556
00:40:38,637 --> 00:40:40,770
There sure are a lot of
swelled heads around though.

557
00:40:42,574 --> 00:40:44,640
You might say that.

558
00:40:46,744 --> 00:40:49,878
What I really want
is to just be with you,

559
00:40:50,981 --> 00:40:53,448
and do fun things

560
00:40:53,584 --> 00:40:56,418
and go out and stay in.

561
00:40:56,754 --> 00:40:59,857
And just be free for once in my life.

562
00:41:01,725 --> 00:41:04,760
You examine me, Miss Eyre.

563
00:41:04,928 --> 00:41:08,197
- You think me handsome?
- No, sir.

564
00:41:09,968 --> 00:41:11,662
By my word,

565
00:41:11,762 --> 00:41:15,652
there is something singular about you.

566
00:41:16,140 --> 00:41:20,192
When one asks you
a question you... you...

567
00:41:21,345 --> 00:41:23,849
You rap out a round rejoinder,

568
00:41:23,949 --> 00:41:28,584
which if not blunt, is at least brusque.

569
00:41:29,253 --> 00:41:32,224
Sir, I beg your pardon,
I spoke too plain.

570
00:41:32,524 --> 00:41:35,594
I ought to have replied that beauty
is of little consequence,

571
00:41:35,694 --> 00:41:37,262
or something of the sort.

572
00:41:37,362 --> 00:41:40,765
You ought to have replied no such thing.
Beauty of little consequence, indeed.

573
00:41:40,865 --> 00:41:44,299
Indeed. Indeed.

574
00:41:46,403 --> 00:41:50,475
And so, under the pretense of softening,

575
00:41:50,575 --> 00:41:53,011
your previous outrage now,

576
00:41:53,111 --> 00:41:56,381
you stick a penknife under my ear.

577
00:41:56,481 --> 00:41:59,715
What fault do you find with me, pray?

578
00:42:01,385 --> 00:42:03,903
I can't believe it.

579
00:42:07,124 --> 00:42:11,062
- Who does this clown think he is?
- I told you not to read that.

580
00:42:11,162 --> 00:42:13,932
They never ever a kind word, if they did,
they probably misspell it.

581
00:42:14,732 --> 00:42:18,770
Goes after the actress, too.
You should have used Bev.

582
00:42:20,171 --> 00:42:24,843
Well, I had a really
disastrous day myself.

583
00:42:24,943 --> 00:42:27,946
I'm sorry, what happened?

584
00:42:28,046 --> 00:42:32,082
I got a letter from Bev's father
asking me for a divorce.

585
00:42:32,182 --> 00:42:36,251
- And he's not giving us a penny.
- Oh, that's terrible.

586
00:42:37,287 --> 00:42:40,355
- I'm so sorry.
- Yeah.

587
00:42:40,591 --> 00:42:42,727
You know, I was mad for that man.

588
00:42:42,827 --> 00:42:46,630
I met him when he was the bartender
at the Roosevelt Hotel.

589
00:42:46,730 --> 00:42:51,566
I was a waitress working for tips and
going up for auditions whenever I could.

590
00:42:52,136 --> 00:42:56,671
- You were an actress?
- No, I was a dancer.

591
00:42:57,709 --> 00:43:00,676
And not half bad, actually.

592
00:43:01,679 --> 00:43:03,814
I got a callback
for a Fred and Ginger movie.

593
00:43:03,914 --> 00:43:05,981
- Really?
- Yes.

594
00:43:07,518 --> 00:43:10,688
One night after work
we were going up Highway 1,

595
00:43:10,788 --> 00:43:13,525
to this little beach
that we liked and, oh,

596
00:43:13,625 --> 00:43:17,762
we'd been drinking,
and Herb took a turn too quickly

597
00:43:17,862 --> 00:43:21,299
and the next thing I knew,
I was in the hospital

598
00:43:21,399 --> 00:43:25,123
and the doctor was telling me
that he'd taken off my leg.

599
00:43:25,769 --> 00:43:27,632
Poor thing.

600
00:43:28,277 --> 00:43:29,807
That's awful.

601
00:43:29,907 --> 00:43:32,149
But when Bev was born,

602
00:43:32,576 --> 00:43:37,115
she was such a special child,

603
00:43:37,415 --> 00:43:43,485
and I felt as if she had been
given to me to make up for my leg.

604
00:43:44,221 --> 00:43:49,002
- Of course.
- It was as if it had been pre-ordained.

605
00:43:49,102 --> 00:43:54,116
Everything that has gone on
has felt as if it was...

606
00:43:54,216 --> 00:43:56,231
pre-ordained.

607
00:43:58,502 --> 00:44:02,474
You've done a marvelous job
raising Woodsey.

608
00:44:02,574 --> 00:44:07,075
No, no, you are a superb mother.

609
00:44:08,746 --> 00:44:12,280
- Thank you. I tried.
- Yeah.

610
00:44:13,051 --> 00:44:16,318
My own mother was a class A cunt.

611
00:44:16,620 --> 00:44:18,323
- Errol. Oh.
- Oh, no, no.

612
00:44:18,423 --> 00:44:22,624
She did despicable things
to me and to my father.

613
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:25,327
Destructive woman.

614
00:44:26,130 --> 00:44:30,434
Yeah, I'm sure Mr. Freud would say that
she had a large hand in shaping my

615
00:44:30,534 --> 00:44:32,537
distinctive attitude toward women.

616
00:44:32,637 --> 00:44:35,507
But you're a gentleman among gentlemen.

617
00:44:35,807 --> 00:44:41,877
Florence, I am and always will be,
quite literally, an absolute son of a bitch.

618
00:44:43,581 --> 00:44:46,184
- Cheers.
- And you know it. Cheers.

619
00:44:46,284 --> 00:44:49,217
- To hell of a day.
- To hell of a day.

620
00:44:50,053 --> 00:44:54,059
- So, what happened next?
- Well, then after the play closed,

621
00:44:54,159 --> 00:44:58,730
Errol's luck changed and he got a call
from the top director, John Huston,

622
00:44:58,830 --> 00:45:02,067
who asked him to be in his new film,
The Roots of Heaven

623
00:45:02,167 --> 00:45:06,571
and that starred Juliette Gréco
and Orson Welles.

624
00:45:06,671 --> 00:45:10,106
The only bad thing was
that it was in Africa.

625
00:45:17,881 --> 00:45:21,553
<i>Woodsey, it's incredible to me
that love would exist</i>

626
00:45:21,653 --> 00:45:25,156
<i>between a man my age and one so young.</i>

627
00:45:25,256 --> 00:45:29,628
<i>But I do so want to believe that you mean
what you've been writing to me.</i>

628
00:45:29,728 --> 00:45:33,098
<i>It might seem unbelievable
that a man as masculine as Errol</i>

629
00:45:33,198 --> 00:45:38,433
<i>would weep while writing a love letter,
but there's no doubt that he did.</i>

630
00:45:41,171 --> 00:45:42,579
<i>Beverly loved those letters,</i>

631
00:45:42,679 --> 00:45:46,177
<i>they were the only thing
that kept her going with him away.</i>

632
00:45:46,277 --> 00:45:48,814
<i>But afterwards,
she just missed him more.</i>

633
00:45:49,614 --> 00:45:52,384
<i>And then something happened
that took us both by surprise,</i>

634
00:45:52,484 --> 00:45:55,120
<i>Errol landed a part for Bev in the film,</i>

635
00:45:55,220 --> 00:45:58,907
<i>but it turned out,
that old fox had a trick up his sleeve.</i>

636
00:45:59,022 --> 00:46:01,760
- I'm sorry, no.
- Mom, come on.

637
00:46:01,860 --> 00:46:05,664
It will be a cold day in hell
before I let you go that far without me.

638
00:46:05,764 --> 00:46:08,266
It's not my fault that he could only
get them to pay for one ticket.

639
00:46:08,366 --> 00:46:10,001
Yeah, I'm sure he tried very hard.

640
00:46:10,101 --> 00:46:14,405
- Please, please, please...
- Baby, just stop it. Just stop it.

641
00:46:14,505 --> 00:46:18,643
This isn't a day trip to the Santa Monica
Pier that we're talking about here.

642
00:46:18,743 --> 00:46:21,045
But I would be with Errol,
you know he'd look after everything...

643
00:46:21,145 --> 00:46:25,617
There are bugs and animals and diseases
and God knows what else.

644
00:46:25,717 --> 00:46:27,986
Well, fine. I'll just go,
you can't stop me.

645
00:46:28,086 --> 00:46:30,388
You just try it, missy,
and you see how far you get.

646
00:46:30,488 --> 00:46:34,356
Mom, it's a big movie with major stars.

647
00:46:35,359 --> 00:46:39,731
I have to say I'm really amazed you'd
want me to pass up an opportunity like this,

648
00:46:39,831 --> 00:46:42,564
it goes against everything
you've ever taught me.

649
00:46:43,400 --> 00:46:45,934
Unless you don't think I'm up to it.

650
00:46:46,270 --> 00:46:48,003
That's ridiculous.

651
00:46:49,773 --> 00:46:52,596
<i>So she went to Africa, all that way,</i>

652
00:46:52,696 --> 00:46:58,146
<i>and she would write me these wonderful
little postcards saying how hot it was.</i>

653
00:46:58,448 --> 00:47:01,920
<i>All of the cast and crew came down
with dysentery except for Errol,</i>

654
00:47:02,020 --> 00:47:04,653
<i>who was avoiding drinking water.</i>

655
00:47:10,460 --> 00:47:14,633
<i>I stayed on in New York and picked up
a job in a nearby movie theater.</i>

656
00:47:14,733 --> 00:47:18,002
<i>The pay wasn't bad
and the people were all right.</i>

657
00:47:18,102 --> 00:47:19,804
<i>One week they were playing Errol's movie</i>

658
00:47:19,904 --> 00:47:23,542
<i>and I really got a hoot
out of telling folks all about him.</i>

659
00:47:24,142 --> 00:47:27,579
<i>In the end I decided to go home
to California and wait for Beverly.</i>

660
00:47:27,679 --> 00:47:33,014
<i>And when she came back we clicked into our
routine just like she'd never been away.</i>

661
00:47:34,251 --> 00:47:36,488
- That's Katonga.
- Katonga, okay.

662
00:47:36,588 --> 00:47:39,223
- He was so nice.
- Sweet.

663
00:47:40,625 --> 00:47:43,294
- Is that a rat?
- No, no. That's Riki.

664
00:47:43,394 --> 00:47:46,161
- Oh, Riki?
- He was my pet mongoose.

665
00:47:48,231 --> 00:47:50,569
- Oh, God, looks like so much fun.
- It was.

666
00:47:51,269 --> 00:47:54,304
I ate so much,
the desserts were so good.

667
00:47:54,704 --> 00:47:56,671
This was our hotel.

668
00:47:57,674 --> 00:47:59,208
And here's us in Madrid.

669
00:48:00,444 --> 00:48:03,058
We didn't stay there for very long.

670
00:48:03,847 --> 00:48:08,186
- This is the Mediterranean Sea.
- Oh, so calm.

671
00:48:08,286 --> 00:48:09,888
Yeah, I know.

672
00:48:09,988 --> 00:48:12,790
This is on Errol's yacht,
the Zaca, in Majorca.

673
00:48:12,890 --> 00:48:15,343
- Such a beautiful boat.
- So beautiful.

674
00:48:16,359 --> 00:48:17,463
I almost forgot,

675
00:48:18,363 --> 00:48:21,366
I have a little, welcome home...

676
00:48:21,466 --> 00:48:23,567
Just a little something for you.

677
00:48:23,667 --> 00:48:26,377
Thank you. That's so sweet.

678
00:48:29,106 --> 00:48:31,711
It's a Paula Lynn.

679
00:48:31,875 --> 00:48:34,843
Oh, that's nice thank you, Mom.

680
00:48:36,780 --> 00:48:39,851
Of course, if you don't really
care for it, you can exchange it.

681
00:48:39,951 --> 00:48:41,386
- No. No, I really like it.
- My feelings won't be hurt.

682
00:48:41,486 --> 00:48:44,343
- It's really pretty. I like it.
- Fine.

683
00:48:44,443 --> 00:48:46,454
Florence.

684
00:48:46,723 --> 00:48:49,092
- Errol.
- Drink?

685
00:48:49,394 --> 00:48:51,796
Why not, what are we drinking?

686
00:48:51,896 --> 00:48:54,769
We're drinking your health, of course.

687
00:48:55,365 --> 00:48:57,636
- So nice to see you.
- Thank you.

688
00:48:57,736 --> 00:49:01,739
I can hardly believe that we actually
made it back in one piece

689
00:49:01,839 --> 00:49:05,507
from the bowels of darkest Africa.

690
00:49:05,742 --> 00:49:07,876
- Here you are.
- Thank you.

691
00:49:08,045 --> 00:49:09,920
You're younger.

692
00:49:10,248 --> 00:49:12,517
- Doesn't Woodsey look well?
- Beautiful.

693
00:49:12,617 --> 00:49:15,820
Light of my life. Fire of my loins.

694
00:49:15,920 --> 00:49:18,823
- You remember where that's from?
- That book by Nabokov.

695
00:49:18,923 --> 00:49:21,258
You see how I'm educating her.

696
00:49:21,358 --> 00:49:24,125
Yes, well...

697
00:49:24,561 --> 00:49:28,730
Ladies, if you will excuse me,
I'll go slip into something more dignified.

698
00:49:33,503 --> 00:49:37,372
Oh, I'm so glad you're back,
both of you.

699
00:49:39,342 --> 00:49:41,579
Does he seem maybe just a little...

700
00:49:41,679 --> 00:49:44,048
- I don't know, off?
- He's fine, Mom.

701
00:49:44,148 --> 00:49:49,253
But you wouldn't notice because
you see him every day, but he seems...

702
00:49:49,353 --> 00:49:51,956
- I don't know, something's going on.
- He has back pain, that's all.

703
00:49:52,056 --> 00:49:54,258
That's what it is.
Is he seeing a doctor?

704
00:49:54,358 --> 00:49:55,494
- Yes.
- Okay.

705
00:49:55,594 --> 00:49:58,927
Just drop it. I'm gonna
get another box of slides.

706
00:50:00,263 --> 00:50:03,167
Woodsey, why are you
so dressed all the time?

707
00:50:03,267 --> 00:50:05,433
Grab a hat, would you?

708
00:50:11,442 --> 00:50:13,341
Flo, pardon.

709
00:50:37,234 --> 00:50:39,369
One line, that's it?

710
00:50:39,469 --> 00:50:42,673
- I had more, they cut it out.
- I don't believe it.

711
00:50:42,977 --> 00:50:44,675
- I'm furious with the studio.
- Good job, Errol.

712
00:50:44,775 --> 00:50:47,045
Yeah, thank you very much, thank you.

713
00:50:47,145 --> 00:50:50,081
You know, they always do it,
they cut the best scenes.

714
00:50:50,181 --> 00:50:52,947
- They cut a lot of my lines, as well.
- Can't you do something about it?

715
00:50:53,047 --> 00:50:56,587
No, no, no. They're a hard-headed lot.

716
00:50:56,687 --> 00:50:59,390
I gave you up for five months
and that's it?

717
00:50:59,490 --> 00:51:02,093
- I had a great time.
- That's not the point, is it?

718
00:51:02,193 --> 00:51:05,730
I don't know, Florence,
I think perhaps happiness is the point.

719
00:51:05,830 --> 00:51:09,634
At the end of the day, more important
than stardom and Hollywood.

720
00:51:09,734 --> 00:51:13,438
Fame is like a religion
in this godless country.

721
00:51:13,538 --> 00:51:16,541
It only provides the public
with idols that they can worship

722
00:51:16,641 --> 00:51:20,044
and then tear down
as the mood strikes them.

723
00:51:20,144 --> 00:51:21,679
Don't change the subject.

724
00:51:21,779 --> 00:51:25,013
She hasn't had a shot, you said you'd
give her a shot, she hasn't had one.

725
00:51:30,787 --> 00:51:33,922
- How's your health?
- Never better.

726
00:51:35,125 --> 00:51:37,730
People say you drink too much.

727
00:51:38,830 --> 00:51:41,132
If you believed all the rumors about me,

728
00:51:41,232 --> 00:51:45,400
I'd think you were... I'd think I was
something quite extraordinary.

729
00:51:46,203 --> 00:51:49,437
I have to say the idea
definitely intrigues me.

730
00:51:49,673 --> 00:51:54,245
- Errol Flynn as Humbert Humbert.
- Yes, it's the part of a lifetime.

731
00:51:54,345 --> 00:51:57,968
I was born to play it really, you know,
I think this chap Nabokov is a genius.

732
00:51:58,068 --> 00:51:59,816
I love that book.

733
00:51:59,916 --> 00:52:01,814
Yes, and I think for the role of Lolita

734
00:52:01,914 --> 00:52:05,720
you'll agree that Beverly
has all the right prerequisites.

735
00:52:07,257 --> 00:52:10,595
- How did her audition for you go?
- Not well.

736
00:52:10,795 --> 00:52:12,897
Oh, you're not gonna find
a better Lolita.

737
00:52:12,997 --> 00:52:16,133
- You can search all you want.
- No dice, Errol.

738
00:52:16,233 --> 00:52:17,899
Besides, she's too old.

739
00:52:19,035 --> 00:52:21,002
That's a shame.

740
00:52:22,839 --> 00:52:24,742
I think you ought to
rethink this, Kubrick,

741
00:52:24,842 --> 00:52:28,176
because you see,
we're sort of a package deal.

742
00:52:28,411 --> 00:52:30,445
You're not serious?

743
00:52:32,516 --> 00:52:34,849
Well, that makes things...

744
00:52:36,019 --> 00:52:37,652
Awkward.

745
00:52:49,066 --> 00:52:53,604
<i>Just when Hollywood closed its doors,
Errol had a terrific idea.</i>

746
00:52:53,704 --> 00:52:57,742
<i>He'd always been fascinated
by the ideology behind rebel causes.</i>

747
00:52:57,842 --> 00:53:01,545
<i>So, he flew to Cuba and began work
on an independent movie</i>

748
00:53:01,645 --> 00:53:04,846
<i>in support of
the rebel chief Fidel Castro.</i>

749
00:53:08,085 --> 00:53:11,419
<i>This time, it was no
bit part for Beverly.</i>

750
00:53:22,465 --> 00:53:26,938
Are all you Americans so bloodthirsty?
This isn't even your war.

751
00:53:27,038 --> 00:53:31,909
I don't even know who those guys Batista
and Castro are. That's your problem.

752
00:53:32,009 --> 00:53:36,114
But the man I'm gonna marry is out there
in that stinking, lousy jungle hiding.

753
00:53:36,214 --> 00:53:39,150
And if he has a reason for it, so can I.

754
00:53:39,250 --> 00:53:42,919
I wish some of the Cubans
felt as strongly as you do.

755
00:53:43,019 --> 00:53:43,717
Cut.

756
00:53:45,121 --> 00:53:47,755
Wonderful, moving on.

757
00:53:50,493 --> 00:53:52,430
- Nice take.
- Oh, thanks.

758
00:53:52,530 --> 00:53:55,233
- I'm serious.
- Goofball.

759
00:53:55,333 --> 00:54:00,070
So we got... three hours
of sun and five scenes.

760
00:54:00,329 --> 00:54:04,305
Here's what I think you should do.
You should do...

761
00:54:04,641 --> 00:54:07,111
- It's nicer over here in Cuba.
- Yeah.

762
00:54:07,211 --> 00:54:10,845
Beverly, I know flirting when I see it,
and that was flirting.

763
00:54:11,514 --> 00:54:15,616
What am I supposed to do, he was
talking to me, I was only talking back.

764
00:54:16,019 --> 00:54:21,626
While you're here, making this movie
with me, you will behave appropriately.

765
00:54:21,726 --> 00:54:24,868
- Got it?
- What are you, my parent?

766
00:54:25,395 --> 00:54:27,862
Don't dare try that with me.

767
00:54:32,335 --> 00:54:34,169
Hello.

768
00:54:56,426 --> 00:55:00,428
- Here you go, Mr. Flynn.
- Thank you, old sport.

769
00:55:00,797 --> 00:55:04,832
- Where's Miss Woodsey today?
- She's...

770
00:55:05,335 --> 00:55:09,370
- Out and about.
- She's very young.

771
00:55:11,374 --> 00:55:13,038
Yes.

772
00:55:13,743 --> 00:55:17,948
I'm far too old for her, but sadly,

773
00:55:18,048 --> 00:55:21,180
she's not too young for me.

774
00:55:22,752 --> 00:55:27,225
Mr. Flynn, there's a place
that's not too far from here,

775
00:55:27,325 --> 00:55:31,927
they have plenty girls,
and very young and very beautiful.

776
00:55:33,530 --> 00:55:35,797
I'm sure they are.

777
00:55:37,033 --> 00:55:39,934
Thanks old boy, not today.

778
00:55:41,137 --> 00:55:42,804
Excuse me.

779
00:56:08,631 --> 00:56:11,619
- Hello.
- Hello.

780
00:56:12,168 --> 00:56:14,135
You're mad at me?

781
00:56:14,404 --> 00:56:17,463
Is there a reason
I should be mad at you?

782
00:56:17,563 --> 00:56:18,464
No.

783
00:56:19,442 --> 00:56:21,609
Then I'm not mad.

784
00:56:22,512 --> 00:56:24,555
You surprise me.

785
00:56:26,050 --> 00:56:29,083
I surprise even myself sometimes.

786
00:56:44,467 --> 00:56:46,037
They are having a ball out there.

787
00:56:46,437 --> 00:56:50,871
And Beverly's career
is taking off in leaps and bounds.

788
00:56:51,975 --> 00:56:53,644
That Errol's a marvel.

789
00:56:54,779 --> 00:56:57,212
Errol Flynn.
They don't make them like that anymore.

790
00:56:57,814 --> 00:57:01,919
Yeah, he's... He's a rascal, that one.

791
00:57:02,019 --> 00:57:04,622
He's always playing pranks.
I mean, it's just so much fun.

792
00:57:04,722 --> 00:57:07,088
To be around him, you know.

793
00:57:07,657 --> 00:57:09,554
I miss him.

794
00:57:21,338 --> 00:57:23,571
You're burning up.

795
00:57:41,558 --> 00:57:45,295
- It's malaria. It's come back.
- I think we should get a doctor.

796
00:57:45,630 --> 00:57:47,462
No, no.

797
00:57:48,431 --> 00:57:51,099
Look, maybe they could
give you something.

798
00:57:52,101 --> 00:57:54,935
Just hold me. Just hold me.

799
00:58:01,144 --> 00:58:03,634
I'm dying, Woodsey.

800
00:58:04,414 --> 00:58:06,247
No, you're not.

801
00:58:06,916 --> 00:58:08,601
I am.

802
00:58:09,819 --> 00:58:11,688
I feel it.

803
00:58:11,788 --> 00:58:14,590
- I feel it.
- You are not.

804
00:58:24,000 --> 00:58:27,270
I am the...

805
00:58:27,370 --> 00:58:30,327
most selfish man in the world.

806
00:58:30,427 --> 00:58:32,435
Don't be silly.

807
00:58:33,476 --> 00:58:36,380
All my life, I've done
what the hell I wanted.

808
00:58:36,480 --> 00:58:39,247
And to hell with the consequences.

809
00:58:41,050 --> 00:58:44,314
I'm dragging you down with me.

810
00:58:51,594 --> 00:58:55,730
- What have I done to you?
- Errol, stop.

811
00:58:56,799 --> 00:59:00,902
This is crazy. Just rest.

812
00:59:04,507 --> 00:59:06,690
You'll be okay.

813
00:59:08,611 --> 00:59:10,593
You'll be okay.

814
00:59:42,545 --> 00:59:43,788
Good morning, Woodsey.

815
00:59:45,682 --> 00:59:47,631
Morning.

816
00:59:49,986 --> 00:59:53,956
Do me a favor, would you, darling?
Bring me that flask.

817
00:59:54,056 --> 00:59:56,266
I think you should drink water.

818
00:59:57,594 --> 00:59:59,728
Water is just for swimming in,
I've told you that.

819
01:00:03,766 --> 01:00:05,933
Are you gonna be okay?

820
01:00:07,403 --> 01:00:12,273
Yes, I actually think the worst is over.

821
01:00:12,975 --> 01:00:15,209
For this round.

822
01:00:15,611 --> 01:00:19,149
- You need to rest for a few days.
- Yes, ma'am.

823
01:00:19,582 --> 01:00:22,286
I want you to get me
a clean sheet of paper.

824
01:00:22,386 --> 01:00:24,618
I want you to write
something down for me.

825
01:00:24,718 --> 01:00:26,253
What?

826
01:00:26,656 --> 01:00:30,091
- Just do it, would you?
- Not until you tell me.

827
01:00:34,831 --> 01:00:39,536
Just in case anything happens,
I want to make things right with you.

828
01:00:39,636 --> 01:00:42,439
To make an amendment
to my will, that's all.

829
01:00:42,539 --> 01:00:45,573
What are you talking about?
You're gonna be fine.

830
01:00:46,175 --> 01:00:47,781
Just do it.

831
01:00:56,219 --> 01:00:59,186
- There's some notepaper.
- Good enough.

832
01:01:05,094 --> 01:01:08,462
I, Errol Thomson Flynn,

833
01:01:10,466 --> 01:01:15,135
being of sound mind and body...

834
01:01:18,641 --> 01:01:21,308
am hereby dictating

835
01:01:22,879 --> 01:01:26,213
my last will and testament.

836
01:01:38,094 --> 01:01:42,496
<i>When they came back from Cuba,
it was time to throw a party.</i>

837
01:01:43,966 --> 01:01:48,305
<i>Beverly's 17th birthday was coming up,
so Errol splashed out.</i>

838
01:01:48,405 --> 01:01:52,418
<i>He hired a band and invited
some of his Hollywood crowd.</i>

839
01:01:53,242 --> 01:01:55,112
<i>All of Beverly's high school
friends turned up.</i>

840
01:01:55,212 --> 01:01:59,447
<i>And I think they were amazed to see
what a star she had become.</i>

841
01:02:04,620 --> 01:02:06,554
Go, Daniel.

842
01:02:13,062 --> 01:02:14,978
Darling, that was beautiful.

843
01:02:15,664 --> 01:02:17,598
Oh, God.

844
01:02:28,847 --> 01:02:29,773
Everyone.

845
01:02:31,347 --> 01:02:35,016
Ladies and gentlemen, friends...

846
01:02:35,451 --> 01:02:37,321
new friends, old friends,

847
01:02:37,421 --> 01:02:41,822
I have a formal announcement I'd like
to make concerning our birthday girl.

848
01:02:42,425 --> 01:02:47,364
I want the world to take note
that Miss Beverly Aadland, a lovely girl,

849
01:02:47,464 --> 01:02:51,766
somewhere between
the ages of five and 50...

850
01:02:52,169 --> 01:02:57,138
will soon become
the fourth and final Mrs. Flynn.

851
01:03:02,813 --> 01:03:06,201
<i>Happy birthday, happy, happy birthday</i>

852
01:03:06,301 --> 01:03:07,848
<i>Happy birthday</i>

853
01:03:07,948 --> 01:03:09,725
Happy, darling?

854
01:03:11,755 --> 01:03:14,391
We did it, baby. We did it.

855
01:03:17,194 --> 01:03:21,865
<i>And I hope
that all your dreams come true</i>

856
01:03:21,965 --> 01:03:25,502
<i>Happy birthday, happy, happy birthday</i>

857
01:03:25,602 --> 01:03:28,035
<i>Happy birthday</i>

858
01:03:28,135 --> 01:03:32,007
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

859
01:03:39,181 --> 01:03:42,483
- There you are. Enjoy.
- Oh, thank you.

860
01:03:43,686 --> 01:03:45,920
Congratulations, Florence.

861
01:03:46,020 --> 01:03:48,525
- Oh, Madge, thank you for coming.
- Such a swell night.

862
01:03:48,625 --> 01:03:50,694
- I had so much fun.
- Oh, good.

863
01:03:50,794 --> 01:03:52,096
Beverly looks so beautiful.

864
01:03:52,196 --> 01:03:55,164
I know, she's gonna
make a beautiful bride.

865
01:03:55,264 --> 01:03:58,702
You never told me. How did she
ever meet Errol in the first place?

866
01:03:58,802 --> 01:04:01,238
Well, I think it was fate.

867
01:04:01,447 --> 01:04:03,674
You see, she was passing
for 18 at the studio,

868
01:04:03,774 --> 01:04:07,444
so I couldn't really tag along.
Mama couldn't just tag along, you know.

869
01:04:07,544 --> 01:04:10,948
So, I wasn't there when they got together.
But she told me everything.

870
01:04:11,448 --> 01:04:12,783
- Beverly?
- Oh, are you leaving?

871
01:04:12,883 --> 01:04:13,884
Yes, yeah.

872
01:04:13,984 --> 01:04:17,287
She was a virgin and he made
love to her on the first night.

873
01:04:17,387 --> 01:04:20,124
And he was so crazy for her
that he tore her dress.

874
01:04:20,424 --> 01:04:24,928
Yes, it was a $75 bolero Paula Lynn.

875
01:04:25,028 --> 01:04:27,331
Can you imagine, but, you know,
what was she gonna do?

876
01:04:27,431 --> 01:04:29,699
- It's Errol Flynn.
- My God.

877
01:04:29,878 --> 01:04:31,398
Baby!

878
01:04:32,601 --> 01:04:36,006
- You remember Madge from the nail salon.
- What are you doing?

879
01:04:36,106 --> 01:04:38,776
What do you... Oh, it's okay. It's okay.

880
01:04:38,876 --> 01:04:42,579
Madge is good people
and she's been following your career.

881
01:04:42,679 --> 01:04:45,916
- It's private.
- Don't you talk to me that way.

882
01:04:46,016 --> 01:04:47,321
I'll see you ladies later.

883
01:04:48,785 --> 01:04:50,554
Why do you keep telling everyone?
It's none of their business.

884
01:04:50,654 --> 01:04:53,490
- I know who I can trust and who I can't.
- No, you don't.

885
01:04:53,590 --> 01:04:56,326
Yes, I do and look,
just because you're engaged to Errol,

886
01:04:56,426 --> 01:04:59,930
doesn't mean that you own him lock,
stock and barrel. He's my friend, too.

887
01:05:00,030 --> 01:05:02,666
- He's my fiancé, not yours, Mom.
- Obviously.

888
01:05:02,766 --> 01:05:04,267
So stay out of it.

889
01:05:04,367 --> 01:05:07,437
Just how far do you think you would have
gotten with this thing if it weren't for me?

890
01:05:07,537 --> 01:05:10,941
- What thing?
- The thing. You and Errol.

891
01:05:11,041 --> 01:05:14,411
Do you know how much I sacrificed
so that you two could be together?

892
01:05:14,511 --> 01:05:17,354
- How much I've...
- It has nothing to do with you. Nothing!

893
01:05:17,454 --> 01:05:21,418
- I lost my home, my marriage. My husband...
- You did it all for yourself.

894
01:05:21,518 --> 01:05:24,015
- I did it for you!
- Leave us alone.

895
01:05:24,115 --> 01:05:27,688
You come back here!
Come back here. You...

896
01:05:28,791 --> 01:05:31,921
What? What are you looking at?

897
01:05:32,761 --> 01:05:34,764
You too.

898
01:05:34,864 --> 01:05:36,600
Mind your own business.

899
01:05:37,400 --> 01:05:39,870
You know, Florence, I was wondering.

900
01:05:39,970 --> 01:05:42,937
I really wanna interview Beverly.

901
01:05:45,074 --> 01:05:46,743
I don't think so.

902
01:05:46,843 --> 01:05:48,912
Maybe she could shed
some new light on some of the...

903
01:05:49,012 --> 01:05:54,215
Beverly doesn't know about the book.
And I don't want to involve her in this.

904
01:05:56,319 --> 01:05:58,555
Well, I'd handle it very gently.

905
01:05:58,655 --> 01:06:02,390
When the time is right, I will tell her.
Not before then.

906
01:06:03,392 --> 01:06:04,880
Okay.

907
01:06:05,162 --> 01:06:07,941
- That's how you feel?
- That's how I feel.

908
01:06:09,231 --> 01:06:10,707
So,

909
01:06:11,537 --> 01:06:13,628
where were we?

910
01:06:18,107 --> 01:06:20,374
The final chapter.

911
01:06:22,144 --> 01:06:26,416
<i>Errol, he wasn't making the kind of money
that he did in his glory days.</i>

912
01:06:26,516 --> 01:06:30,788
<i>And in order to settle his divorce,
he needed some ready cash.</i>

913
01:06:30,888 --> 01:06:34,024
<i>So, even though the Zaca
meant the world to him,</i>

914
01:06:34,124 --> 01:06:36,760
<i>he went up to Vancouver
to sell his yacht.</i>

915
01:06:36,860 --> 01:06:40,627
<i>That shows how much
he loved Bev. Right there.</i>

916
01:06:41,363 --> 01:06:43,066
I'm already getting enquiries.

917
01:06:43,166 --> 01:06:45,468
A treasure hunting expedition
in the Caribbean,

918
01:06:45,568 --> 01:06:48,939
searching for Spanish gold.
Errol Flynn at the helm.

919
01:06:49,039 --> 01:06:51,431
That's a nice idea, sport, but...

920
01:06:51,531 --> 01:06:55,165
need a bit of time to think it over.

921
01:06:55,265 --> 01:06:56,810
Okay.

922
01:06:57,413 --> 01:06:58,891
Well...

923
01:06:59,281 --> 01:07:02,719
- We best be going to the airport.
- Fine. I can drive you there myself.

924
01:07:02,819 --> 01:07:06,354
- Are you sure, sport?
- Are you kidding me? It would be an honor.

925
01:07:07,056 --> 01:07:08,889
What's the matter?

926
01:07:09,425 --> 01:07:11,341
My back.

927
01:07:11,727 --> 01:07:14,331
- Oh, it's killing me.
- I can call a doctor.

928
01:07:14,431 --> 01:07:18,001
No, no, no. I'll be all right.
