Mr. Barrymore's crippled aunt
wanted to view the body.

955
01:09:05,175 --> 01:09:07,077
He slipped the cat 200 smackers,

956
01:09:07,177 --> 01:09:10,747
smuggled the corpus delicti
to my very own home,

957
01:09:10,847 --> 01:09:15,215
where they deposited him
in my favorite armchair.

958
01:09:15,417 --> 01:09:19,319
Well, I got back two hours later.

959
01:09:19,955 --> 01:09:22,191
I was drunk.

960
01:09:22,291 --> 01:09:24,528
Sad drunk.

961
01:09:24,628 --> 01:09:28,098
I opened the door,
flicked on the lights.

962
01:09:28,198 --> 01:09:31,060
And staring right at me,

963
01:09:31,167 --> 01:09:33,171
was John Barrymore.

964
01:09:34,069 --> 01:09:36,973
His eyes were cold.
His expression was...

965
01:09:37,073 --> 01:09:41,609
He was bloodless, gray, bloated.

966
01:09:42,111 --> 01:09:45,015
I let out a gasp. I ran out the door.

967
01:09:45,515 --> 01:09:49,219
I was about to climb into my car and
tear down the hill, when I heard voices.

968
01:09:49,319 --> 01:09:53,957
There on the porch
was Raoul and his cronies,

969
01:09:54,057 --> 01:09:56,704
just as pleased as punch.

970
01:09:58,862 --> 01:10:00,930
What happened to the body, Errol?

971
01:10:01,030 --> 01:10:05,640
Oh, they took it back to the mortuary
and no one was the wiser.

972
01:10:05,902 --> 01:10:09,473
But if I know Barrymore,
he was up on his cloud saying,

973
01:10:09,573 --> 01:10:14,775
"Thanks for the outing, boys.
That last place was a bit cramped."

974
01:10:18,414 --> 01:10:22,426
Is it true you have a two-way mirror
put up in your guestroom?

975
01:10:22,919 --> 01:10:26,556
I'm sorry, young man. I would never
corrupt you with that sordid tale.

976
01:10:26,656 --> 01:10:28,639
Oh, it's all right.
He can hear it, Errol.

977
01:10:29,292 --> 01:10:32,896
To tell you the truth,
I need to lie down for just a bit.

978
01:10:32,996 --> 01:10:34,749
- Do you need me to...
- No, no, no.

979
01:10:36,432 --> 01:10:39,667
Stay there, old sport.
I never felt better in my life.

980
01:10:41,637 --> 01:10:44,605
I shall return.

981
01:11:04,459 --> 01:11:08,896
- So, how do you like Vancouver?
- Oh, it's beautiful. We really like it.

982
01:11:09,565 --> 01:11:12,299
Can I ask how old you are, Beverly?

983
01:11:12,834 --> 01:11:14,503
I'm 21.

984
01:11:14,903 --> 01:11:18,405
Really? You look younger.

985
01:11:18,741 --> 01:11:22,312
I was only 18, when I met Kenneth
and we were in high school.

986
01:11:22,412 --> 01:11:25,846
Excuse me. I'm sorry.
I'm going to check on Errol.

987
01:11:42,397 --> 01:11:44,426
Errol? Errol?

988
01:11:45,400 --> 01:11:48,604
Errol? Is it your back, Errol?

989
01:11:48,704 --> 01:11:53,209
Errol? Help! Someone help me! Please!

990
01:11:53,926 --> 01:11:56,346
Errol? Help!

991
01:11:56,446 --> 01:11:58,904
Help me, someone! Help me!

992
01:11:59,004 --> 01:12:02,316
Help! Please, help!

993
01:12:02,851 --> 01:12:05,087
Errol? Errol!

994
01:12:06,087 --> 01:12:07,701
Errol?

995
01:12:15,530 --> 01:12:17,097
No.

996
01:12:17,199 --> 01:12:19,032
No!

997
01:12:19,568 --> 01:12:21,802
Errol, no!

998
01:12:26,475 --> 01:12:28,378
But is it true Errol Flynn
died in your arms?

999
01:12:28,478 --> 01:12:30,880
- What were his last words?
- How long had you known him?

1000
01:12:30,980 --> 01:12:32,182
Are you going to the funeral?

1001
01:12:32,282 --> 01:12:34,657
Miss Aadland, did Flynn
leave you anything in his will?

1002
01:12:36,785 --> 01:12:39,289
- Beverly! Bev!
- Miss Aadland, how did you meet...

1003
01:12:39,389 --> 01:12:40,821
How old are you?

1004
