01:13:35,278 --> 01:13:38,215
<i>about contributing
to the delinquency of a minor.</i>

1014
01:13:38,315 --> 01:13:44,017
<i>Keep it up and you'll end up
right where you belong, in the clink.</i>

1015
01:13:53,630 --> 01:13:56,905
Bev! Oh, I'm so glad to see you.

1016
01:13:57,005 --> 01:14:00,036
I missed you so much. Come on.

1017
01:14:00,136 --> 01:14:03,039
You look tired. Have you been sleeping?

1018
01:14:03,139 --> 01:14:07,476
I'm fine. I just... just wanted
to stay out of the spotlight.

1019
01:14:07,776 --> 01:14:11,844
I know. It's... It's been very hard.

1020
01:14:13,916 --> 01:14:18,120
I fixed up the bedroom
for you very nicely.

1021
01:14:19,155 --> 01:14:20,724
And I'll just... I'll stay on the couch.

1022
01:14:20,824 --> 01:14:24,103
Oh, no, it's okay.
I'm fine with the couch.

1023
01:14:27,095 --> 01:14:28,828
Mom?

1024
01:14:29,264 --> 01:14:33,770
There's all this crazy stuff in the press
about me being pregnant, and the will.

1025
01:14:33,870 --> 01:14:36,491
It makes me so damned mad.

1026
01:14:37,205 --> 01:14:40,709
- Have you been talking to them?
- No, not really.

1027
01:14:41,009 --> 01:14:42,495
Well, don't.

1028
01:14:44,913 --> 01:14:48,451
She's not great. She's only been sleeping
about two hours at a time.

1029
01:14:48,551 --> 01:14:51,321
And she doesn't eat...
I didn't know what was wrong.

1030
01:14:51,421 --> 01:14:55,792
So I took her to the doctor and the
doctor said that she's just grief-stricken.

1031
01:14:55,892 --> 01:14:59,796
- <i>Well, she's been through a lot.</i>
- I know, Ronnie. I know.

1032
01:14:59,896 --> 01:15:01,530
That's why I thought
it would be a good idea

1033
01:15:01,630 --> 01:15:05,168
for her to just... You know,
throw herself into something.

1034
01:15:05,268 --> 01:15:08,772
Like her career.
Take advantage of all the attention.

1035
01:15:08,872 --> 01:15:13,009
In fact, there's a guy out in Glendale
who wants her to appear in his nightclub.

1036
01:15:13,109 --> 01:15:15,942
It's just the ticket for Bev, I think.

1037
01:15:35,097 --> 01:15:38,368
<i>Some say that happiness</i>

1038
01:15:38,468 --> 01:15:42,539
<i>Is hard to find</i>

1039
01:15:42,639 --> 01:15:45,775
<i>Some say they'd never</i>

1040
01:15:45,875 --> 01:15:48,978
<i>Have peace of mind</i>

1041
01:15:49,078 --> 01:15:52,482
<i>I say the same thing</i>

1042
01:15:52,582 --> 01:15:55,918
<i>And I thought it was true</i>

1043
01:15:56,018 --> 01:16:00,081
<i>But that was before</i>

1044
01:16:00,181 --> 01:16:03,626
<i>I met you</i>

1045
01:16:03,726 --> 01:16:06,863
<i>Some say that life</i>

1046
01:16:06,963 --> 01:16:10,766
<i>Is a mystery</i>

1047
01:16:10,866 --> 01:16:14,105
<i>Some say that love</i>

1048
01:16:14,205 --> 01:16:17,604
- <i>Brings only misery</i>
- Asshole.

1049
01:16:17,704 --> 01:16:21,163
<i>I say the same thing</i>

1050
01:16:21,263 --> 01:16:24,707
<i>And I thought it was true</i>

1051
01:16:24,807 --> 01:16:30,784
<i>But that was before I met you</i>

1052
01:16:31,319 --> 01:16:33,957
Hank Segal of the Times loved you.

1053
01:16:34,057 --> 01:16:36,960
And the Hollywood Post
is gonna write a little article.

1054
01:16:37,060 --> 01:16:41,864
And Pat is so happy because the take
at the bar was twice what it normally is.

1055
01:16:41,964 --> 01:16:44,199
That's 'cause you were here.

1056
01:16:44,499 --> 01:16:47,170
Very funny. So...
What do you say we celebrate

1057
01:16:47,270 --> 01:16:50,773
and go, maybe, to Canter's
and get a burger and a shake?

1058
01:16:50,873 --> 01:16:54,140
I can't. I'm going to a party
at Jack's tonight.

1059
01:16:55,110 --> 01:16:56,779
I don't like you hanging out
with those punks.

1060
01:16:56,879 --> 01:17:00,149
They are... They just play up to you because
you're famous and because of Errol...

1061
01:17:00,249 --> 01:17:03,717
- That's not true.
- You be home by midnight.

1062
01:17:22,670 --> 01:17:24,443
Beverly?

1063
01:17:26,374 --> 01:17:27,943
Bev?

1064
01:17:35,016 --> 01:17:37,050
Wait here.

1065
01:17:42,458 --> 01:17:46,194
- Yeah, who is it?
- <i>I wanna talk to Beverly.</i>

1066
01:17:46,294 --> 01:17:48,631
- Who is this?
- I have to talk to Beverly.

1067
01:17:48,731 --> 01:17:51,634
If you don't let me talk to her,
I'm gonna call the police.

1068
01:17:51,734 --> 01:17:54,616
- <i>Sleep it off, lady.</i>
- Wait a minute.

1069
01:18:20,295 --> 01:18:21,928
Beverly?

1070
01:18:22,497 --> 01:18:23,647
Beverly?

1071
01:18:27,869 --> 01:18:28,911
Beverly!

1072
01:18:32,207 --> 01:18:34,006
Beverly!

1073
01:18:34,506 --> 01:18:36,545
Beverly, it's your mother!

1074
01:18:36,645 --> 01:18:39,949
- She's out of her mind.
- She's baying at the moon.

1075
01:18:40,049 --> 01:18:42,785
- Beverly!
- Go home, lady!

1076
01:18:42,885 --> 01:18:45,188
- What?
- Go home!

1077
01:18:45,288 --> 01:18:47,335
But I want my daughter here!
Is she up there?

1078
01:18:47,435 --> 01:18:49,292
- Beverly? Send her down!
- I haven't seen her!

1079
01:18:49,392 --> 01:18:52,861
Yes, you have! You liar!
Get me my daughter!

1080
01:18:53,390 --> 01:18:54,330
Bev!

1081
01:18:56,031 --> 01:19:00,236
What? What the fuck
are you doing, you jackass?

1082
01:19:00,336 --> 01:19:02,539
Come down... stop it!

1083
01:19:03,139 --> 01:19:06,075
What are you doing? Beverly!

1084
01:19:06,175 --> 01:19:09,710
I'm gonna get the law after you,
you stupid punks!

1085
01:19:10,913 --> 01:19:12,712
Go home!

1086
01:19:33,668 --> 01:19:36,271
I called as soon as I saw the papers.

1087
01:19:36,671 --> 01:19:40,476
- When's the court date?
- 23rd of next month.

1088
01:19:40,576 --> 01:19:42,945
- It's hard to believe, really.
- I know.

1089
01:19:43,045 --> 01:19:45,958
Contributing to the delinquency
of a minor and then they take Bev

1090
01:19:46,058 --> 01:19:50,153
and they hold her in juvenile hall,
what is the point of that?

1091
01:19:50,553 --> 01:19:52,827
They're just trying to
punish me for what Errol did.

1092
01:19:56,424 --> 01:19:59,428
- It'll never stand up in court.
- Why?

1093
01:19:59,528 --> 01:20:04,267
It's got a lot of major difficulties. I mean,
it's in Beverly's handwriting for a start.

1094
01:20:04,367 --> 01:20:05,735
And that really wouldn't be
such a problem,

1095
01:20:05,835 --> 01:20:09,572
except for when you look on the back,
there's no signature page.

1096
01:20:09,772 --> 01:20:13,640
- It's gotta be there, somewhere.
- No, not on this copy.

1097
01:20:15,443 --> 01:20:18,615
He dictated it to Beverly,
so he must have signed it.

1098
01:20:18,715 --> 01:20:21,250
I mean, he wanted Beverly
to have a third of his estate.

1099
01:20:21,350 --> 01:20:23,720
Well, his estate is,
believe me, a nightmare.

1100
01:20:23,820 --> 01:20:26,589
I don't really care.
You've gotta find the signature page.

1101
01:20:26,689 --> 01:20:28,858
But Florence, it's more than that.

1102
01:20:28,958 --> 01:20:34,494
He needed to initial every page in the
presence of a witness, two witnesses.

1103
01:20:35,431 --> 01:20:37,864
This is a sloppy job.

1104
01:20:38,499 --> 01:20:39,932
Typical.

1105
01:21:23,311 --> 01:21:26,582
- Are you eating? You look thin.
- No, I'm fine.

1106
01:21:26,782 --> 01:21:31,387
- They taking good care of you?
- Yeah, they're really nice.

1107
01:21:31,587 --> 01:21:35,522
Don't worry, baby. We're gonna
be back together again real soon.

1108
01:21:39,427 --> 01:21:42,598
Mom, people are saying that they're
never gonna give you custody.

1109
01:21:42,798 --> 01:21:45,531
What? Who's saying that?

1110
01:21:45,901 --> 01:21:50,236
Just people around here.
My social worker and stuff.

1111
01:21:50,572 --> 01:21:54,310
Well, that's not true. I've spent my
last dime on a crackerjack attorney

1112
01:21:54,410 --> 01:21:56,179
and I'm fighting
with everything that I've got.

1113
01:21:56,579 --> 01:21:58,344
I know.

1114
01:22:00,748 --> 01:22:03,719
But I just wanted to say
that if it doesn't go your way,

1115
01:22:03,819 --> 01:22:07,456
they've talked to me about some
foster care at a ranch outside the city.

1116
01:22:07,556 --> 01:22:09,258
No, that's not gonna happen.
That's not gonna happen.

1117
01:22:09,358 --> 01:22:12,056
It's not the way it's meant to be.

1118
01:22:13,061 --> 01:22:15,832
I don't think that anything
was ever meant to be, Mom.

1119
01:22:16,032 --> 01:22:18,710
I disagree.

1120
01:22:21,370 --> 01:22:23,825
All right, I don't wanna argue about it.

1121
01:22:31,746 --> 01:22:33,880
Bev, I...

1122
01:22:34,917 --> 01:22:39,322
I went to see the lawyer
about the will and...

1123
01:22:39,422 --> 01:22:42,589
It's no good.
He doesn't think it's gonna hold up.

1124
01:22:43,858 --> 01:22:47,363
But, Errol dictated it
to me himself in Cuba.

1125
01:22:47,463 --> 01:22:50,667
I know, I know, I know.
But they can't find the signature page.

1126
01:22:50,767 --> 01:22:54,933
And they don't know if it was stolen
or it was misplaced. Then he didn't...

1127
01:22:55,271 --> 01:22:59,444
He didn't file the damn
thing properly. It's just...

1128
01:23:00,042 --> 01:23:02,475
Left us high and dry.

1129
01:23:04,846 --> 01:23:07,113
Well, I don't care.

1130
01:23:09,584 --> 01:23:12,118
I don't care about the money.

1131
01:23:13,488 --> 01:23:16,622
I don't care about anything, really.

1132
01:23:18,294 --> 01:23:20,415
There's nothing that can bring him back.

1133
01:23:20,962 --> 01:23:23,296
I know, baby.

1134
01:23:25,401 --> 01:23:28,935
It was a party
whenever he was around, wasn't it?

1135
01:23:29,971 --> 01:23:33,773
Now, the party's over
and we have to clean up the mess.

1136
01:23:38,680 --> 01:23:40,983
But, actually, Bev...

1137
01:23:41,083 --> 01:23:43,429
Something has...

1138
01:23:43,985 --> 01:23:48,129
come up that might be
a silver lining to all of this.

1139
01:23:49,557 --> 01:23:51,687
There's an offer of a book.

1140
01:23:52,627 --> 01:23:56,198
It would be about you and me and Errol,
and I've been talking to this writer.

1141
01:23:56,298 --> 01:23:59,835
He seems like a good guy
and he says it's a slam dunk.

1142
01:23:59,935 --> 01:24:02,604
- Mom, don't.
- What?

1143
01:24:02,704 --> 01:24:07,355
Don't do that. Don't talk to him.

1144
01:24:08,009 --> 01:24:11,280
- Bev, did you love Errol?
- Of course.

1145
01:24:11,380 --> 01:24:14,918
Well, don't you think that you owe to him
to tell the real story of your love?

1146
01:24:15,418 --> 01:24:18,854
I mean, all the gutter versions
are out there.

1147
01:24:18,954 --> 01:24:21,891
Now is our chance
to set the record straight,

1148
01:24:21,991 --> 01:24:25,868
to tell the world what a good man
he was and how much he loved you.

1149
01:24:29,531 --> 01:24:31,238
Bev, you're still so young.

1150
01:24:32,133 --> 01:24:37,170
When you get to be my age, you realize
that life just goes by in a minute.

1151
01:24:37,905 --> 01:24:40,643
This is our chance to make our mark.

1152
01:24:40,743 --> 01:24:43,713
All those people that are clucking
their tongues at us,

1153
01:24:43,813 --> 01:24:46,782
they don't have what we have.
They don't have our real story.

1154
01:24:46,882 --> 01:24:50,617
A love story that will stand
the test of time.

1155
01:24:51,386 --> 01:24:55,625
People will know who we are,
a hundred years from now.

1156
01:24:55,925 --> 01:24:59,692
But none of that matters
once you're gone.

1157
01:25:00,662 --> 01:25:02,033
Look at Errol.

1158
01:25:02,133 --> 01:25:06,202
Look at Errol. He is still here,
because he's Robin Hood,

1159
01:25:06,302 --> 01:25:09,305
the swashbuckler, and people remember.

1160
01:25:09,405 --> 01:25:11,904
Have you signed anything with him?

1161
01:25:12,440 --> 01:25:14,262
Not yet.

1162
01:25:15,076 --> 01:25:17,243
Well, don't.

1163
01:25:17,945 --> 01:25:21,948
- Promise me that you won't.
- Oh, Beverly.

1164
01:25:24,870 --> 01:25:28,154
Promise me,
or you'll never see me again.

1165
01:25:38,199 --> 01:25:40,307
All right, I promise.

1166
01:25:40,702 --> 01:25:42,376
Thank you.

1167
01:25:44,472 --> 01:25:46,606
I love you, Mom.

1168
01:25:50,611 --> 01:25:53,085
I love you, baby.

